---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Elara Voss"
  description="Privacy policy for elaravoss.dev. Information about how contact enquiries and site usage data are handled in compliance with GDPR."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-accent text-sm font-mono tracking-wide uppercase mb-3">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted text-sm">Last updated: May 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        This privacy policy explains how Elara Voss (&ldquo;I&rdquo;, &ldquo;me&rdquo;, &ldquo;my&rdquo;) collects,
        uses, and protects personal data in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and
        applicable Dutch law. This policy applies to the website at <a href="https://elaravoss.dev">elaravoss.dev</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Who is responsible for your data?</h2>
      <p>
        Elara Voss, sole trader, Amsterdam, Netherlands.<br />
        Contact: <a href="mailto:hello@elaravoss.dev">hello@elaravoss.dev</a>
      </p>

      <h2>What data is collected and why?</h2>

      <h3>Email enquiries</h3>
      <p>
        When you email me at hello@elaravoss.dev, I collect the email address you send from and the contents
        of your message. I use this information solely to respond to your enquiry and assess whether I am a
        good fit for your project. Legal basis: legitimate interest (GDPR Art. 6(1)(f)).
      </p>

      <h3>Server logs</h3>
      <p>
        This site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may process your IP address and browser information
        in server logs for security and performance purposes. I do not have access to individual log records.
        See <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Cloudflare&rsquo;s privacy policy</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h3>No cookies, no analytics</h3>
      <p>
        This website does not set any cookies. I do not use Google Analytics, Meta Pixel, or any other
        third-party tracking scripts. There is no advertising, no remarketing, and no cross-site tracking.
      </p>

      <h2>How long is data retained?</h2>
      <p>
        Email correspondence is retained for as long as the client relationship is active, plus two years
        thereafter for administrative purposes. If no project results from an enquiry, correspondence is
        deleted within six months.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights under GDPR</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access the personal data I hold about you</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data (&ldquo;right to be forgotten&rdquo;)</li>
        <li>Object to processing based on legitimate interest</li>
        <li>Data portability (receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format)</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with the Dutch Data Protection Authority (<a href="https://www.autoriteitpersoonsgegevens.nl" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens</a>)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:hello@elaravoss.dev">hello@elaravoss.dev</a>.
        I will respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        This site uses no third-party services that receive personal data, with the exception of Cloudflare
        (infrastructure) as noted above.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If I make material changes to this policy, I will update the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above.
        Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
